PN,42402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1780441387
OL,3,CFamily of teenager swept to sea
OL,4,Cquestion emergency response at inquest
OL,6,FToday (Monday 1 June) an inquest was
OL,7,Fresumed with a tribute from her
OL,8,Ffamily. It read: "She was perfect and
OL,9,Fdeeply loved. She had an amazing smile
OL,10,Fand wonderful sense of humour. She
OL,11,Floved her family and her friends
OL,12,Fdeeply... Her death has left a
OL,13,Fprofound and devastating void in our
OL,14,Flives."
OL,16,FThe inquest heard that the teenager -
OL,17,Fand a friend - were sat on steps
OL,18,Foverlooking the beach, when a large
OL,19,Fsurge of water suddenly swept her into
OL,20,Fthe sea on Thursday 24 July 2025.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,425,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1780441387
OL,3,CFamily of teenager swept to sea
OL,4,Cquestion emergency response at inquest
OL,6,FThe weather that day was good, but the
OL,7,Fsea was rough and the waves very
OL,8,Fstrong. Edie was described as a
OL,9,F'capable swimmer,' but struggled in
OL,10,Fthe conditions and was soon washed
OL,11,Ffurther along the coast.
OL,13,FSpeaking at the inquest, a
OL,14,Frepresentative from HM Coastguard at
OL,15,Fthe scene described the rescue as
OL,16,F'very challenging' due to the location
OL,17,Fand conditions of the sea.
OL,19,F"It was the worst place to be at that
OL,20,Ftime," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,425,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1780441387
OL,3,CFamily of teenager swept to sea
OL,4,Cquestion emergency response at inquest
OL,6,FHe described the waves as having a
OL,7,F"like a washing-machine effect." And,
OL,8,Fat the location, "there is no out,
OL,9,Fwith high walls, making the rescue
OL,10,Fdifficult."
OL,12,FThe inquest also examined response
OL,13,Ftimes from some of the emergency
OL,14,Fservices and teams involved, how they
OL,15,Fcommunicated with each other, and some
OL,16,Fthe decisions that were made.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,425,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F424A1780441387
OL,3,CFamily of teenager swept to sea
OL,4,Cquestion emergency response at inquest
OL,6,FMr Scott, representing the family,
OL,7,Fquestioned whether HM Coastguard,
OL,8,Fwhich was co-ordinating the response
OL,9,Ffrom its base in Humberside, could -
OL,10,Fand should - have dispatched an
OL,11,Fambulance to the scene sooner.
OL,13,FTo which it was replied that the
OL,14,Fclosest and fastest available
OL,15,Fresources were sent - though it was a
OL,16,Fhigh pressure day, during peak season.
OL,18,FThe family has previously praised the
OL,19,Fbravery of those involved in the
OL,20,Frescue.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
